MY BEST LUNCH TIPS 🔥⬇️🍱
1) Make eating easier: Partially (or fully) peel the mandarin so that they don’t have to fumble with it and lose precious eating time at school. 🍊 Cut things into smaller bite-size pieces. Send snack-y lunches that are easy to munch on whilst talking to friends. 🍎🧀🥨
2) Sometimes less is more. Lunchtime is often super short — so don’t overwhelm your kiddo with too much food that is just going to go to waste. 🕛
3) Keep things balanced by including protein, fiber, healthy fat, veggies, and fruit.. and of course, lots of color! 🌈 This has been my go-to method since 2015!
4) Remember that things can change even within the same school year. 📝🫣🫠🥹 Communicate with your kiddo about what is working, what isn’t... and get their input. You’re in this together 🙌
5) Don’t be afraid to supplement with some store-bought items — things like @feel.sunnie pizza dippers, @sunbutter jammies, @myserenitykids pouches, grocery store sushi, etc... 🍕🍓
-
In this lunchbox:
💗 Buffalo Chicken Wrap in a roasted red pepper lavash
💗 @simplemills veggie pizza popmmm’s
💗 @mooncheesesnacks
💗 a mandarin, partially peeled
💗 a homemade trail mix (made with roasted cashews, peanut M&Ms, golden raisins, and pretzels)
-

Milkshakes might bring all the boys to the yard, but Baked Brie is bringing all the moms. 😉🧀

Grab a mom friend (or 2️⃣) and make my delicious Baked Brie with a Lemon Cherry Compote and chopped pistachios! 🍋🍒 It’s perfect for summer entertaining or an impromptu patio hangout while the kids play. ☀️
-
Set everything out on a big cutting board and follow my 2s rule - 2 fruits (🍎+🍒), 2 veggies (🫑+🍅), 2 crackers, 2 sweets (fruit jellies and @sietefoods choc chip cookies), 2 nuts (cashews and pistachios) etc.

Why do this ⤵️🌟
Add a bit of cuteness & whimsy without much effort! 💪😍🤩🍱 Using a simple star cutter has been one of my go-to lunchbox moves since literally 2016 (checked my order history, lol 😆). It’s great for sandwiches or just cutting fruits & veggies.🌟

Cut a small star out of the top slice of bread and let the sandwich toppings shine through:
1️⃣: Add a slice of strawberry for PB&J (also helps the jam not ooze out!) 🍓
2️⃣: @tillamook cheese shows through on the #orangeweek sandwich I made on the live show of @goodmorningamerica awhile back! (Turkey/cheese) 🧡🧀🥕
3️⃣: Let colorful cream cheese shine through for a BIG pop of color (cream cheese/cucumber sammie) 🥒💗

I also use the small star cut-out for like small bites of something... one bite of a bell pepper (not my daughter’s all time favorite veggie, but one small star bite is a good start), a decorative star bite of apple or strawberry, etc... 🌶️🫑🍓🍉🥭

Comment ‘STAR’ for the link to the star cutter straight to your DMs ⭐️📲💌
https://amzn.to/3rTqaeB

I’m all about cute, colorful food — but it has to be SIMPLE —> @eattherainbow_kids 🌈
